title: Axiom mission arrives at ISS
summary: A SpaceX Crew Dragon spacecraft carrying four private astronauts arrived at the International Space Station April 9 for a scheduled eight-day stay.

title: Citing valve problem, NASA will load only the SLS core stage in next countdown test
summary: A problem with a helium valve on the Space Launch System moon rocket’s upper stage will require ground teams to only partially load the giant launcher with cryogenic propellants during an upcoming countdown dress rehearsal, NASA officials said Saturday. NASA also confirmed teams now targeting Thursday for the next try to complete the test.

title: Axiom-1 arrives at ISS for science-packed week on orbit
summary: Crew Dragon Endeavour has successfully docked to the Node-2 zenith port — otherwise called the Harmony space-facing port — at 8:29 am EDT (12:29 UTC) after launching at 11:17 am EDT (15:17 UTC) the previous day. Docking was delayed for nearly 45 minutes due to an issue with a video uplink to the ISS while holding at Waypoint 2.

title: Vega C to launch Sentinel-1C in 2023
summary: The European Space Agency will launch its Sentinel-1C radar imaging satellite on a Vega C rocket in 2023 as the agency continues to study potential impacts of Russia’s invasion of Ukraine on that launch vehicle.

title: First-of-its-kind commercial astronaut mission heads for space station
summary: Strapped in the seats of a SpaceX crew capsule, a retired NASA astronaut and three wealthy paying passengers rocketed into orbit Friday from the Kennedy Space Center on the first fully commercial mission to the International Space Station.

title: SpaceX launches first all-private astronaut crew to the International Space Station
summary: A SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket and Crew Dragon spacecraft have successfully begun the first all-private astronaut mission to an orbital space station...

title: Axiom Private Astronauts Headed to International Space Station
summary: Four private astronauts are in orbit following the successful launch of Axiom Mission 1 (Ax-1), the first all private astronaut mission to the International Space Station.

title: SpaceX launches commercial mission to ISS
summary: SpaceX launched a Crew Dragon spacecraft April 8 carrying four commercial astronauts to the International Space Station for Axiom Space.

title: Dragon launches, carrying four private citizens to the space station [Updated]
summary: Crew expected to dock with the ISS on Saturday for an eight day mission.

title: Axiom-1 launches first ever private crewed mission to ISS
summary: SpaceX and Axiom Space launched the AX-1 mission to the International Space Station (ISS) on Friday, April 8, 2022, at 11:17:11 am EDST / 15:17:11 UTC from LC-39A at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida.
